Libya - A.Libya: The fragile revivial of the teaching of English in Libya

Maralavana Ilangovan - The National

For eight months now, a linguistics degree holder and a former finance department employee of a gas company is holding session every Sunday in Tripoli for instructors on the basics of teaching English.

Feras Alzoubi, 26, had managed to enrol a handful of Libyans for his programme, but says he wants 200 in his classes. The programme aims to rehabilitate the estimated 30,000 English teachers who quit Libya due to the ousted Gaddafi regime's suspected plots against "traitorous" Libyan teachers.

Bahrain - Bahrain is planning to ban rugby because the demands of the sport constrain it from being able to compete in international tournaments.

Al Jazeera

Bahrain is developing a proposal to ban rugby in the kingdom due to "financial, logistical and suitability of the physical demand of the sport", the Bahrain Olympic Committee has confirmed.
